def: The state of being jetty; blackness. Pennant.
A flying off in small particles, as heated iron or fermentingliquors; a sparkling; scintillation. Sir T. Browne.
A woman's girdle; a cestus. [R.] Collins.
A violent and widely extended change in the surface of theearth, as, an elevation or subsidence of some part of it, effected byinternal causes. Whewell.
A corner. [Obs.]Lurking in hernes and in lanes blind. Chaucer.
The act of turning into allegory, or of understanding in anallegorical sense.
A knot of ribbons worn by a guest at a wedding; a weddingfavor. [Obs.]
Short of, or lacking the regular number of, servants orhelpers.
Firm; determined; fixed. "A most posed . . . and gravebehavior." [Obs.] Urquhart.
